This is a gstreamer plugin for recognition
of specific images in a video stream.

The video stream can be a video file 
or a video stream
and the collection of images 
can be changed dynamically 
sending a message to the plugin.

The plugin uses OpenCV for the recognition of images.

The plugin uses OpenCV for the recognition of images.

To use it on Ubuntu, first install the dependencies :
> sudo apt-get install gstreamer-0.10 gstreamer-base-0.10 gstreamer-plugins-base-0.10 opencv libgst-ruby

Then compile the plugins with :

> sudo ./configure --prefix=/usr
> sudo make
> sudo make install

Then go to the script directory and launch the analysis of a video with :

> cd scripts
> ruby videofeed.rb ../data/slides.mp4 ../data/images

this script takes two additional optional arguments :

* algorithm [ 'histogram' or 'surf' ( default ) ] : algorithm used for detection
* tolerance [ 0.10 by default ] : distance tolerance for similarity

For any more information or support, contact ydegoyon@gmail.com.
